Defendant in custody on WRIT.
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing having been convicted of 2nd degree sexual assault/use of force on 10-17-16.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eighteen (18) years.  That is ten (10) years initial confinement followed by eight (8) years extended supervision consecutive to sentence defendant is serving in 96 CF 131.
The defendant is not found eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)  Defendant shall not ingest any drugs or alcohol (maintain absolute sobriety);
2)  Defendant shall submit to random drug screens and pay for same;
3)  Defendant shall not enter into any taverns or bars, nor shall he work in any establishment that serves alcohol; 
4)  Defendant will not be in possession of any controlled substances unless prescribed by a physician, taken in prescribed doses;
5)  Defendant shall follow any, and all, recommendations by the Department regarding assessments and treatment, which may include AODA, Psychological, Sex Offender Treatment, and any cognitive intervention programming;
6)  Defendant shall comply with the sex offender registry;
7)  Pay costs of the action; and
8)  Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Defendant is to be given 401 days jail credit.
Minutes.
